# Sangster static site

This is a static, multi-page HTML site (portfolio / product narrative). Keep edits consistent with existing patterns.

## Stack & structure
- **No build step**: plain HTML, CSS, and vanilla JS. Inline `<style>` and `<script>` are used per page; shared assets: `raycast-bg.css`, `mobile.css`, `favicon.svg`, `auth-check.js`.
- **Assets**: Images under `assets/images/` (e.g. `finaldesign-0.png`, `anatomy.png`). Logos under `assets/logos/`. Use lowercase filenames and correct extension (e.g. `anatomy.png` not `anatomy.PNG`).

## Page shell
- Every page: `<meta charset="UTF-8" />`, `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />`, `<link rel="icon" href="favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />`.
- Font: Inter (and Sometype Mono where used). Typical: `font-family: "Inter", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;`.
- Left nav: same hamburger + overlay + drawer markup/script across pages; mark current page with class `current` and `aria-current="page"`.

## Typography & UI
- **Page title (h1)**: Use `font-weight: 600` for the main page heading (e.g. `.page-title`, `.projects-title`, `.exp-title`, `.phil-title`, `.about-title`, `.cover-title`, `.workflow-title`, `.why-title`, `.ux-title`, `.di-title`, `.thanks-title`). Keep card/section headings (e.g. h2) at 700 when they should stay bolder.
- **Highlighted text**: Use `font-weight: 700` for highlight spans (e.g. `.highlight`, `.why-highlight`, `.highlight-yellow`).
- **Buttons/links**: Secondary style: border `#c7d2fe` or `#e5e7eb`, hover lighten; “Next” links with arrow SVG and consistent padding.

## Cards & layout
- **Glass-style cards**: `backdrop-filter: blur(16px)`, `background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2–0.4)`, rounded corners (e.g. 24px), subtle border and inset shadow. Hover: slight `translateY(-4px)` and stronger shadow unless “no hover” is requested.
- **Icons in cards**: Often 24×24px SVG, light stroke (`stroke-width: 1.5`), muted color (e.g. `#64748b`). Use consistent bottom margin (e.g. 40px, 100px, or 160px as specified).

## Workflows (current-workflow.html, workflow.html)
- Step boxes: `.step-box`, `.flow-arrow`, reveal by adding `.revealed` and updating step index. “Expand All” / “Collapse All” toggles: track expanded state and swap label; on collapse, hide second row and reset step indices.
- **Compare view** (workflow.html): Current workflow section hidden by default; “Compare with old flow” appears after future steps are open; compare mode = two-column layout, current left / future right; “Close compare” exits.

## Micro-interactions
- Prefer CSS: `transition`, `@keyframes`, `animation-delay` for stagger. Easing: `cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)` for smooth finish.
- Delayed UI (e.g. “Next” button): use `setTimeout` and a `.visible` class with opacity/visibility transition; avoid removing the element from the DOM.

## Do not
- Introduce a build step, framework, or new global CSS file without being asked.
- Change favicon or asset paths to uppercase extensions; keep references like `anatomy.png`, `finaldesign-0.png`.

